Owing to the high cases of piracy and sea robbery within the Gulf of Guinea, the International Maritime Bureau has ranked the region as one of the most troubled waterways, after the Gulf of Aden. For more on this Channel Africa spoke to Max Williams, Chief Operating Officer at Africa Risk Compliance, a security consultancy based in London.. --ChannelAfrica--